# Frontend Routing

## Library

react-router v2 (`^2.7.0`). Uses `Router`, `Route`, `IndexRoute`, `browserHistory`. Do NOT use v4/v5/v6 APIs.

## Route configuration

All routes in `client/src/configureRoutes.tsx`, nested under `<Route component={App}>` so the App shell wraps every page:

| Path | Component |
|------|-----------|
| `/` | `WelcomePage` |
| `/owners/list` | `FindOwnersPage` |
| `/owners/new` | `NewOwnerPage` |
| `/owners/:ownerId/edit` | `EditOwnerPage` |
| `/owners/:ownerId/pets/:petId/edit` | `EditPetPage` |
| `/owners/:ownerId/pets/new` | `NewPetPage` |
| `/owners/:ownerId/pets/:petId/visits/new` | `VisitsPage` |
| `/owners/:ownerId` | `OwnersPage` |
| `/vets` | `VetsPage` |
| `/error` | `ErrorPage` |
| `*` | `NotFoundPage` |

## Navigation

- Use `this.context.router.push({ pathname, query })` for programmatic navigation (requires `static contextTypes = { router: React.PropTypes.object.isRequired }`)
- Use `<Link to="...">` from react-router for declarative navigation
- `browserHistory` requires `historyApiFallback` in the dev server to return `index.html` for all paths
